               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280529-239-person1296">
                  JOSEPH 
                  LLOYD
               <interp inst="t18280529-239-person1296" type="surname" value="LLOYD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-239-person1296" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-239-person1296" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a watchman. I met the prisoner on Sunday evening, the 4th of May, about ten o'clock, at the top of East-street, Hoxton, about two hundred yards from Mr. Salter's with a bundle - I asked what was in it, he said some washing; I took it from under his arm, and seeing some hair and the rest of these articles in it, I took him to the watch-house.</p>
               <p>JOHN SALTER. I am a <rs id="t18280529-239-viclabel1315" type="occupation">horse-hair manufacturer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280529-239-victim1295 t18280529-239-viclabel1315"></join>, and live at <placeName id="t18280529-239-crimeloc1316">Hoxton</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280529-239-crimeloc1316" type="placeName" value="Hoxton"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280529-239-crimeloc1316" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280529-239-off1313 t18280529-239-crimeloc1316"></join>. On Sunday, the 4th of May, I went out at four o'clock in the afternoon, leaving my door on the single lock; I came home about eleven o'clock at night - I had drunk rather more than had done me good; the door was locked - I went in and went up to bed - my wife perceived the things disturbed; we had left nobody at home; we looked and missed these articles from the first-floor front room.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. BARRY. Q. Had you been drinking before you left home? A. I had taken a little - I know I pulled the door too.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280529-239-person1297">
                  CHARLES 
                  CONSTABLE
               <interp inst="t18280529-239-person1297" type="surname" value="CONSTABLE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-239-person1297" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-239-person1297" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The prisoner was brought to the watch-house; I searched him and found some picklock keys, a crow-bar, and phosphorus box on him.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I had been drinking - I heard a cry, ran out to see what it was, and these things lay in the road - I took them up.</p>
               <p>
